column25: Level of business relationship B2B Special strengths: GM-free and strong organic focusAGRANA processes and adds value to corn, potatoes and wheat to make a wide range of differentiated starch products. These are then supplied to the food and semiluxury food industry as well as to non-food industries such as the paper, textiles, cosmetics, bioplastics or construction material industry. column25: Level of business relationship B2B Special strengths: GM-free and strong organic focusAGRANA processes and adds value to corn, potatoes and wheat to make a wide range of differentiated starch products. These are then supplied to the food and semiluxury food industry as well as to non-food industries such as the paper, textiles, cosmetics, bioplastics or construction material industry. In the Starch segment, we are active in Austria and Eastern Europe with a total of five production sites.

column25: Its our mission to shake up the industry and to make organic ingredients more widely available and more affordable in the market.  We want to go back to the way nature intended it, and working along with our farmers we source and produce the best quality organic dried ingredients directly from origin and delivering them right to your warehouse. Following rigorous standards of excellence, we control every part of the process from volume, quality, and homogeneity, along with making sure your product always meets our strict European standards. So this includes certifying that it is free of unwanted pesticides, herbicides, and heavy metals. We always keep up to our commitment to deliver what we promise - at our cost.

column25: Its our mission to shake up the industry and to make organic ingredients more widely available and more affordable in the market.  We want to go back to the way nature intended it, and working along with our farmers we source and produce the best quality organic dried ingredients directly from origin and delivering them right to your warehouse. Following rigorous standards of excellence, we control every part of the process from volume, quality, and homogeneity, along with making sure your product always meets our strict European standards. So this includes certifying that it is free of unwanted pesticides, herbicides, and heavy metals. We always keep up to our commitment to deliver what we promise - at our cost.

column25: Robis SL, born in 1983 in Granada (Spain) in order to seek the health of people through natural medicine and disease prevention through the use of medicinal plants and food supplements.Its beginnings are linked to a philosophy of life based on respect for others and for the environment that surrounds it, in a time that is beginning to create concerns about the benefits of natural medicine, Robis born to research and create health from a new viewpoint.From the point of view of health it is now in nature. Therefore, Robis is one of the pioneering companies in its sector working mainly on care for people from the standpoint of manufacturing quality by nature.Robis commitment to in-house production and quality as keys to distinguished his 30 years as a manufacturer garantee.The company began selling in Spain, where it is important and has a large presence, highlighting its range of royal jelly, which is a flagship product in that market. The years and craftsmanship have led the company to extend for several countries. Among its line of ecological or bio products (biological) are: Royal Jelly, Desmodium, digestive infusion, draining infusion, hepatic infusion, laxative tea, valerian, yeast, complex detox (artichoke, black radish, milk thistle and green tea ).

column25: Its our mission to shake up the industry and to make organic ingredients more widely available and more affordable in the market.  We want to go back to the way nature intended it, and working along with our farmers we source and produce the best quality organic dried ingredients directly from origin and delivering them right to your warehouse. Following rigorous standards of excellence, we control every part of the process from volume, quality, and homogeneity, along with making sure your product always meets our strict European standards. So this includes certifying that it is free of unwanted pesticides, herbicides, and heavy metals. We always keep up to our commitment to deliver what we promise - at our cost.

column25: Atilla Sevilmis (founder of Yaban Food) was a businessman based in Istanbul. Over time, his health deteriorated on account of the adverse consequences brought about by the urban life, thus driving him to look for alternative ways of life. He decided to regain his health by altering the way he ate. He started a macrobiotic diet laden with organic food. However, he often failed to find the essential organic foods in the city. To make matters worse, a life full of stress in the city was causing him to feel upset.For this reason, he rented an area of land in south-western Turkey in 1993 at the expense of changing his whole lifestyle. He restored an old house there and started to live in it. Soon, he began to accommodate groups of natural life devotees in his house. He spoiled his guests with naturally-grown products.In the meantime, he kept renting new areas of land on which he grew products with the long-lost seeds of Anatolia. Before long, he began exporting, if in small amounts, bulgur, chickpeas, whole grains, sesame, tahini, dried mulberries, pepper paste, pomegranate syrup to the United States of America.Thats how Yaban was born.Over the course of 19 years that have passed since that time, Yaban has become a company which can offer the most delicious in the most natural way by utilizing the most sophisticated Western techniques and specifications in its food production thanks to its annual projects and a number of dedicated staff.Now the company is managed by his sons Mehmet Firat Sevilmis and Irmak Can Sevilmis .

column25: Level of business relationship B2B Special strengths: GM-free and strong organic focusAGRANA processes and adds value to corn, potatoes and wheat to make a wide range of differentiated starch products. These are then supplied to the food and semiluxury food industry as well as to non-food industries such as the paper, textiles, cosmetics, bioplastics or construction material industry. We also produce bioethanol from corn and crops with a high starch content; this is then used as a petrol additive to make environmentally friendly fuel.AGRANA Starch GmbH oversees the Austrian starch business and coordinates the activities of the subsidiaries and holding companies in Hungary and Romania. In the Starch segment, we are active in Austria and Eastern Europe with a total of five production sites.

column25: Level of business relationship B2B Special strengths: GM-free and strong organic focusAGRANA processes and adds value to corn, potatoes and wheat to make a wide range of differentiated starch products. These are then supplied to the food and semiluxury food industry as well as to non-food industries such as the paper, textiles, cosmetics, bioplastics or construction material industry. We also produce bioethanol from corn and crops with a high starch content; this is then used as a petrol additive to make environmentally friendly fuel.AGRANA Starch GmbH oversees the Austrian starch business and coordinates the activities of the subsidiaries and holding companies in Hungary and Romania. In the Starch segment, we are active in Austria and Eastern Europe with a total of five production sites.

column25: Find more information on us and our products at www.sanabio.bioWe, the SanaBio GmbH, have been producers and distributors of high-quality vegetable oils, gluten-free vegetable and nut flours, and essential oils in the best organic quality for years in the B2B area. Our products are used worldwide as raw materials in the food and cosmetics industries, among others. In recent years, we have also developed into specialists for imports and exports from third countries.Sustainability, i.e., the triad of environmental protection and social responsibility as the basis for economic reasoning, is not a marketing concept for us, but the foundation for all our operational decisions.Hence, you only receive products from certified organic cultivation from SanaBio. In the manufacturing of our products, we try to use as much of nature's treasures as possible. If it cannot be avoided, waste is recycled and returned to the material cycle.

column25: Find more information on us and our products at www.sanabio.bioWe, the SanaBio GmbH, have been producers and distributors of high-quality vegetable oils, gluten-free vegetable and nut flours, and essential oils in the best organic quality for years in the B2B area. Our products are used worldwide as raw materials in the food and cosmetics industries, among others. In recent years, we have also developed into specialists for imports and exports from third countries.Sustainability, i.e., the triad of environmental protection and social responsibility as the basis for economic reasoning, is not a marketing concept for us, but the foundation for all our operational decisions.Hence, you only receive products from certified organic cultivation from SanaBio. In the manufacturing of our products, we try to use as much of nature's treasures as possible. If it cannot be avoided, waste is recycled and returned to the material cycle.

column25: Level of business relationship B2B Special strengths: GM-free and strong organic focusAGRANA processes and adds value to corn, potatoes and wheat to make a wide range of differentiated starch products. These are then supplied to the food and semiluxury food industry as well as to non-food industries such as the paper, textiles, cosmetics, bioplastics or construction material industry. We also produce bioethanol from corn and crops with a high starch content; this is then used as a petrol additive to make environmentally friendly fuel.AGRANA Starch GmbH oversees the Austrian starch business and coordinates the activities of the subsidiaries and holding companies in Hungary and Romania. In the Starch segment, we are active in Austria and Eastern Europe with a total of five production sites.

column25: AgricolliBio Srl is a IMPORTER, EXPORTER and WHOLESALER of Organic Fruits and Vegetables fresh, frozen and dehydrated.Our main goal is to bring primarily Italian and secondly Imported Organic fresh, frozen and dehydrated premium quality fruits and vegetables to the international market, especially our self produced KIWI that we grow on our Fields in Italy and Chile of over 1500HA. The varieties of Kiwi are the Hayward (November-June/July), Soreli (October-December), Green Light which is most similar to the Hayward but is harvested earlier (September-December) and our Chilean Hayward (June/July-September).Our commitment is also dedicated to involve the participation of different agriculture cooperatives spread over Italy, Perù and Chile so that we are able to offer our costumers a wide range of products and to provide an increasingly competitive service in the european and international markets. In comparison to others we are constantly present from the beginning of the growth process to harvest to ensure a sustainable development and quality improvement of all our products. AgricolliBio is looking for sustainable on trust founded Long Term relationships with new costumers all over the wourld.

column25: The Clearspring brand promises premium quality Japanese specialities and Organic Fine Foods that are authentic, versatile and support good health.Made to traditional recipes by master artisan producers, they bring you full, authentic flavours of someof the most exciting food cultures from around the world. They respect local food traditions and are made using finest ingredients without artificial additives, colourings or preservatives.Clearspring always works directly with their producers to build long term partnerships of ethical trade that support sustainable organic farming and benefit local communities. 'Enjoy the great taste of exceptionally good food'.

column25: Find more information on us and our products at www.sanabio.bioWe, the SanaBio GmbH, have been producers and distributors of high-quality vegetable oils, gluten-free vegetable and nut flours, and essential oils in the best organic quality for years in the B2B area. Our products are used worldwide as raw materials in the food and cosmetics industries, among others. In recent years, we have also developed into specialists for imports and exports from third countries.Sustainability, i.e., the triad of environmental protection and social responsibility as the basis for economic reasoning, is not a marketing concept for us, but the foundation for all our operational decisions.Hence, you only receive products from certified organic cultivation from SanaBio. In the manufacturing of our products, we try to use as much of nature's treasures as possible. If it cannot be avoided, waste is recycled and returned to the material cycle.

column25: AgricolliBio Srl is a IMPORTER, EXPORTER and WHOLESALER of Organic Fruits and Vegetables fresh, frozen and dehydrated.Our main goal is to bring primarily Italian and secondly Imported Organic fresh, frozen and dehydrated premium quality fruits and vegetables to the international market, especially our self produced KIWI that we grow on our Fields in Italy and Chile of over 1500HA. The varieties of Kiwi are the Hayward (November-June/July), Soreli (October-December), Green Light which is most similar to the Hayward but is harvested earlier (September-December) and our Chilean Hayward (June/July-September).Our commitment is also dedicated to involve the participation of different agriculture cooperatives spread over Italy, Perù and Chile so that we are able to offer our costumers a wide range of products and to provide an increasingly competitive service in the european and international markets. In comparison to others we are constantly present from the beginning of the growth process to harvest to ensure a sustainable development and quality improvement of all our products. AgricolliBio is looking for sustainable on trust founded Long Term relationships with new costumers all over the wourld.

column25: NutriBoost is a wholesale company / distributor for organic certified superfood, raw food and greens. All our products are certified by SKAL according to EU regulations.Due to our direct contact with local organic certified farmers, farmers organisations and local suppliers, we are able to source the best quality and provide competitive prices. In short NutriBoost offers three different services:1) our own NutriBoost label, ready for retail;2) Private label, including packaging, labelling etc.;3) Bulk delivery.We export on a regular basis and we have all certificates that are needed. By importing and exporting high quality organic certified food products, we try to make these products available to everyone who is investing in their health. We believe that healthy food is the basis of a healthy life. We supply to both small and larger companies.

column25: Its our mission to shake up the industry and to make organic ingredients more widely available and more affordable in the market.  We want to go back to the way nature intended it, and working along with our farmers we source and produce the best quality organic dried ingredients directly from origin and delivering them right to your warehouse. Following rigorous standards of excellence, we control every part of the process from volume, quality, and homogeneity, along with making sure your product always meets our strict European standards. So this includes certifying that it is free of unwanted pesticides, herbicides, and heavy metals. We always keep up to our commitment to deliver what we promise - at our cost.

column25: NutriBoost is a wholesale company / distributor for organic certified superfood, raw food and greens. All our products are certified by SKAL according to EU regulations.Due to our direct contact with local organic certified farmers, farmers organisations and local suppliers, we are able to source the best quality and provide competitive prices. In short NutriBoost offers three different services:1) our own NutriBoost label, ready for retail;2) Private label, including packaging, labelling etc.;3) Bulk delivery.We export on a regular basis and we have all certificates that are needed. By importing and exporting high quality organic certified food products, we try to make these products available to everyone who is investing in their health. We believe that healthy food is the basis of a healthy life. We supply to both small and larger companies.

column25:
Preserva Mundi is a Brazilian company located in São João de Pirabas, Pará State, north of Brazil. 
Our products as well as our business model were structured on the concept of social development. 
We harvest and produce organic products with a critical partnership established with the local community. 
This has not only enhanced the real income of the families living within the micro-region of our plant, but also created the right incentives to explore the Amazon Rain Forest in a sustainable manner, preventing deforestation and adverse social migration. 
Using our own harvested Organic Neen and Noni, Preserva Mundi offers a wide range of exclusive products, catering for both human and non-human uses. These are 100% organic and certified by Control Union ©. Moreover, we also have a select line of special Amazon oils. Our extraction process takes advantage of the social partnership built with the local community to guarantee economic feasibility as well as regional sustainable development.
We have 160,000 neem trees & 10,000 noni trees

column25: Find more information on us and our products at www.sanabio.bioWe, the SanaBio GmbH, have been producers and distributors of high-quality vegetable oils, gluten-free vegetable and nut flours, and essential oils in the best organic quality for years in the B2B area. Our products are used worldwide as raw materials in the food and cosmetics industries, among others. In recent years, we have also developed into specialists for imports and exports from third countries.Sustainability, i.e., the triad of environmental protection and social responsibility as the basis for economic reasoning, is not a marketing concept for us, but the foundation for all our operational decisions.Hence, you only receive products from certified organic cultivation from SanaBio. In the manufacturing of our products, we try to use as much of nature's treasures as possible. If it cannot be avoided, waste is recycled and returned to the material cycle.

column25: Level of business relationship B2B Special strengths: GM-free and strong organic focusAGRANA processes and adds value to corn, potatoes and wheat to make a wide range of differentiated starch products. These are then supplied to the food and semiluxury food industry as well as to non-food industries such as the paper, textiles, cosmetics, bioplastics or construction material industry. We also produce bioethanol from corn and crops with a high starch content; this is then used as a petrol additive to make environmentally friendly fuel.AGRANA Starch GmbH oversees the Austrian starch business and coordinates the activities of the subsidiaries and holding companies in Hungary and Romania. In the Starch segment, we are active in Austria and Eastern Europe with a total of five production sites.

column25: Its our mission to shake up the industry and to make organic ingredients more widely available and more affordable in the market.  We want to go back to the way nature intended it, and working along with our farmers we source and produce the best quality organic dried ingredients directly from origin and delivering them right to your warehouse. Following rigorous standards of excellence, we control every part of the process from volume, quality, and homogeneity, along with making sure your product always meets our strict European standards. So this includes certifying that it is free of unwanted pesticides, herbicides, and heavy metals. We always keep up to our commitment to deliver what we promise - at our cost.

column25: Its our mission to shake up the industry and to make organic ingredients more widely available and more affordable in the market.  We want to go back to the way nature intended it, and working along with our farmers we source and produce the best quality organic dried ingredients directly from origin and delivering them right to your warehouse. Following rigorous standards of excellence, we control every part of the process from volume, quality, and homogeneity, along with making sure your product always meets our strict European standards. So this includes certifying that it is free of unwanted pesticides, herbicides, and heavy metals. We always keep up to our commitment to deliver what we promise - at our cost.

column25: Its our mission to shake up the industry and to make organic ingredients more widely available and more affordable in the market.  We want to go back to the way nature intended it, and working along with our farmers we source and produce the best quality organic dried ingredients directly from origin and delivering them right to your warehouse. Following rigorous standards of excellence, we control every part of the process from volume, quality, and homogeneity, along with making sure your product always meets our strict European standards. So this includes certifying that it is free of unwanted pesticides, herbicides, and heavy metals. We always keep up to our commitment to deliver what we promise - at our cost.

column25:
Preserva Mundi is a Brazilian company located in São João de Pirabas, Pará State, north of Brazil. 
Our products as well as our business model were structured on the concept of social development. 
We harvest and produce organic products with a critical partnership established with the local community. 
This has not only enhanced the real income of the families living within the micro-region of our plant, but also created the right incentives to explore the Amazon Rain Forest in a sustainable manner, preventing deforestation and adverse social migration. 
Using our own harvested Organic Neen and Noni, Preserva Mundi offers a wide range of exclusive products, catering for both human and non-human uses. These are 100% organic and certified by Control Union ©. Moreover, we also have a select line of special Amazon oils. Our extraction process takes advantage of the social partnership built with the local community to guarantee economic feasibility as well as regional sustainable development.
We have 160,000 neem trees & 10,000 noni trees

column25: AgricolliBio Srl is a IMPORTER, EXPORTER and WHOLESALER of Organic Fruits and Vegetables fresh, frozen and dehydrated.Our main goal is to bring primarily Italian and secondly Imported Organic fresh, frozen and dehydrated premium quality fruits and vegetables to the international market, especially our self produced KIWI that we grow on our Fields in Italy and Chile of over 1500HA. The varieties of Kiwi are the Hayward (November-June/July), Soreli (October-December), Green Light which is most similar to the Hayward but is harvested earlier (September-December) and our Chilean Hayward (June/July-September).Our commitment is also dedicated to involve the participation of different agriculture cooperatives spread over Italy, Perù and Chile so that we are able to offer our costumers a wide range of products and to provide an increasingly competitive service in the european and international markets. In comparison to others we are constantly present from the beginning of the growth process to harvest to ensure a sustainable development and quality improvement of all our products. AgricolliBio is looking for sustainable on trust founded Long Term relationships with new costumers all over the wourld.

column25: Find more information on us and our products at www.sanabio.bioWe, the SanaBio GmbH, have been producers and distributors of high-quality vegetable oils, gluten-free vegetable and nut flours, and essential oils in the best organic quality for years in the B2B area. Our products are used worldwide as raw materials in the food and cosmetics industries, among others. In recent years, we have also developed into specialists for imports and exports from third countries.Sustainability, i.e., the triad of environmental protection and social responsibility as the basis for economic reasoning, is not a marketing concept for us, but the foundation for all our operational decisions.Hence, you only receive products from certified organic cultivation from SanaBio. In the manufacturing of our products, we try to use as much of nature's treasures as possible. If it cannot be avoided, waste is recycled and returned to the material cycle.

Preserva Mundi is a Brazilian company located in São João de Pirabas, Pará State, north of Brazil. 
Our products as well as our business model were structured on the concept of social development. 
We harvest and produce organic products with a critical partnership established with the local community. 
This has not only enhanced the real income of the families living within the micro-region of our plant, but also created the right incentives to explore the Amazon Rain Forest in a sustainable manner, preventing deforestation and adverse social migration. 
Using our own harvested Organic Neen and Noni, Preserva Mundi offers a wide range of exclusive products, catering for both human and non-human uses. These are 100% organic and certified by Control Union ©. Moreover, we also have a select line of special Amazon oils. Our extraction process takes advantage of the social partnership built with the local community to guarantee economic feasibility as well as regional sustainable development.
We have 160,000 neem trees & 10,000 noni trees
